<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="434" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Chargé</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-03-28"><hi rend="italic">March 28,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary</hi>: I have the honor to advise your
                            excellency, by order of my Government, that the marriage of His Majesty
                            the King, Don Alfonso XIII, my august sovereign, and Her Highness
                            Princess Victoria Eugenia de Battenberg has been arranged, and that the
                            delegates whom the several countries friendly to Spain may send to the
                            royal wedding should be at Madrid on the 28th of May next.</p>
                        <p>I avail myself, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">L. Pastor.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>